      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ODINS BLACK CROWS (1) was in the money three runs back, missed at his next start, then produced another sound effort at his latest appearance when third at Globe Derby after being handy in the run. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Winning chance. GUEST ARTIST NZ (7) will find this easier than his last-start 11th at Melton and he had some decent NSW form prior. Won his only attempt at this distance and draws for a trail. MISTER BOOMBASTIK (11) has a strong record here which is significant. Finished second over 2190m at this track last time out. A good draw can see a better showing from CAULONIA TERROR (2).",
